<div itemprop="articleBody">
<h1>Tutorial 17. Sewing the Front Princess Seams. Installing the Zipper.</h1>
<p><strong>I sew the front princess seams with a 1.2cm seam allowance. </strong>Be very careful when sewing princess seams for they are the key element on the face of your dress. Moreover, you should make sure not to ease in the central piece made of a single non-duplicated layer of fabric.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I don’t make a bar tack as I stop at the bottom of the skirt</strong> because I want to be able to rip up the seam when evening out the hem of the dress and working with individual layers of fabric.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I have noticed a flaw when examining the princess seam:</strong> I did not pull on the fabric of the side piece hard enough in the curved area of the princess seam, which has resulted in a tuck. I rip up the corresponding area of the princess seam, make additional notches on the side piece, secure the pieces with pins, and re-stitch it. Everything looks great now!</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I sew the other bust princess seam.</strong> I sew over the side piece moving from the end of the iron-on fabric up to the top. Then I turn the garment around and continue sewing the princess seam from the bottom of the skirt up to the point where I started.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image022.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>The princess seam looks very neat and pretty.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image024.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image026.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image028.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I have finished sewing the front princess seams.</strong> And now I only need to press them.</p>
<p><strong>I will install a blind zipper in the back of the dress before sewing down its princess seams.</strong> I have already duplicated the zip-up area of the central back pieces down to the hip line level. My zipper is quite long but I will shorten it later.</p>
<p><strong>I always sew a blind zipper into the back of the dress before sewing down the central seam itself.</strong></p>
<p><strong>The blind zipper will be installed the traditional way:</strong></p>
<p><strong>First I secure the zipper tape in place</strong> by sewing from the very top down to the notch that marks the end of the zipper <strong>using a regular presser foot</strong>.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image030.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image032.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image034.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image036.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image038.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image040.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Then I switch to a specialty blind zipper presser foot and sew it on for good.</strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image042.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image044.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image046.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image048.jpg" alt=""></strong></p>
<p><strong>I close the zipper and check how well it sits in the dress.</strong> It is very important that the top edges of the two halves of the back are placed at the same level.</p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image050.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I trim the seam allowance down to the width of the zipper tape.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image052.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image054.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>Now that I have installed the zipper, I need to sew the central seam at the back of the dress.</strong></p>
<p><strong>I switch to a left-toe presser foot.</strong> I pin together the seam allowances of the zipper, as well as the layers of the skirt, and move the free end of the zipper tape out of the way.</p>
<p><strong>I place the needle in the point where I stopped sewing the zipper, as close as possible to its teeth, and sew a small seam of about 5-7cm with a seam allowance of 2cm.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image056.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image058.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>The zipper blends into the seam very well.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image060.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I switch back to the regular presser foot and continue sewing down the central seam.</strong></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image062.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%207/transcript/Tutorial%2017_files/image064.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p><strong>I make a bar tack across the zipper so I can trim it after pressing the garment.</strong></p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
